250 g Salmon Fillets, skin-on
28 g Baby Spinach
1 unit Tomato
1 unit Green Onion
½ cup Couscous
3 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
½ cup Tikka Sauce
9 g Indian Spice Mix
1 unit Cream Cheese
½ tbsp Butter*
2 tsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat oven to 450˚F.
Wash and dry all produce.
To a medium pot, add 2/3 cup (1 1/3 cups) water, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) butter and 1/8 tsp (1/4) tsp salt. Season with pepper and bring to a boil over high.
Once boiling, stir in couscous. Remove the pot from heat, then cover and set couscous aside for 5 min to rehydrate.

Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Pat salmon dry with paper towels, pressing well to absorb as much moisture as possible. Season with salt, pepper and half the Indian Spice Mix.
Arrange salmon on prepared baking sheet. Drizzle 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil over top.
Roast salmon in the top of the oven for 8-10 min, until cooked through.**

While salmon cooks, roughly chop spinach.
Thinly slice green onion(s).
Cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces.
To a small bowl, add tomato, green onions and 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to mix.

To a small pot, add tikka sauce, cream cheese and remaining Indian Spice Mix. Heat over medium-high for 3-5 min, whisking often until sauce is warmed through and smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff couscous with a fork. Stir in spinach.
Divide couscous and salmon between plates.
Spoon tikka sauce over top.
Drizzle yogurt sauce over top
Spoon marinated tomatoes over top.